# Validation definition for the Aperture autonomous build agent.
# This file is read by the agent to self-verify every goal.
# NEVER edit this file to force a pass.

# "validation" means ALL of the following:
# 1. project_run launches with zero script parse errors (current_run_errors is empty)
# 2. The goal's specific DONE-CHECK passes
# 3. ALL global invariants (DEV-BRAIN.md Part II.5) hold
#
# Global invariants:
# - project_run: zero parse errors.
# - All tests in scenes/_test/ pass.
# - Player never falls through floor or off world (once C2 exists).
# - Codex never loses a discovered node; confidence never silently downgrades (once A3/L2 exist).
# - No autoload throws during _ready().
# - Current main scene always loads.
#
# A goal is DONE only when all three pass simultaneously.
